<a href="/akira/dtd/3049-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_3049">Social Security too Slow&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/4496-4049">brett60johnson</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">7 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">The problem that I see is that Social Security is so far behind in helping people that are disabled for what ever reason, are losing everything including their homes. <br/>I feel that if Social Security worked faster that families would be able to keep their homes and it would help the mortgage companies. And since Social Security would have to hire more people it would put more people to work. So to me it would be a win win for a lot of people. <br/>It is really sad that so many families lose everything just because someone gets sick and can no long work.</div>
