<div id="Idea_2911"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/2911-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_2911">Direct Democracy with Revokable Proxy Voting By Subject&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/4129-4049">bobhilt1</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">8 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Given different expertise levels and passions to engage in certain topics, some people are simply far more expert than others.  If one were able to vote on anything, or alternatively assign one's votes on particular subject areas to someone else they trust to vote wisely, then one could have confidence that their vote is most aligned with their intent.  Proxied votes could be re-proxied to others as desired, potentially creating a strong voting blocks of like-minded individuals.<br/><br/></div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_2911" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_2911', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2242&topicID=2911')">Comments (0)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_2911"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2242">New Strategies and Techniques</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=voting">voting</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=proxy">proxy</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=democracy">democracy</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_2911"></div>
</div></td>
