<div id="Idea_2896"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/2896-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_2896">Reduce impact of Special Interest Groups&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/4078-4049"></a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">8 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">We should keep all US Senators and US Congressmen home in their home states.  They can debate, converse, maintain contact with each other using many different forms of technology.  By have all these representatives at home makes it nearly impossible or cost prohibitive for lobbyists and special interest groups to meet with them on a frequent basis.  It also allows for more easy access to representatives as they will be close to their constituents of their home district.</div>
